{
  "texts": [
    "This fact establishes a crucial link between the m.s.e.",
    "of the reconstruction and antibody nativeness, as the m.s.e.",
    "can be interpreted as the distance of the input sequence from the manifold of native antibodies (Methods).",
    "Reconstruction through the network always introduces some deterioration of the perfect one-hot encoded vectors, meaning that the m.s.e.",
    "is never exactly zero, even when no residue is substituted during inference."
  ]
}